Global Keloid Treatment Market - Industry Overview

Keloid scars are raised, thickened areas of scar tissue that form at the site of an injury or incision, extending beyond the original wound. They occur due to an overproduction of collagen during the healing process, which causes the scar tissue to grow excessively. Factors contributing to keloid formation include genetic predisposition, excessive inflammation, and certain skin types. The global keloid treatment market is experiencing rapid growth owing to developments in treatment technologies, and an increased emphasis on cosmetic as well as dermatological care. The industry offers a wide range of therapies, including corticosteroid injections, cryotherapy, and innovative pharmaceutical techniques. Biotechnology and tailored medications are gaining headway, providing new hope for more effective therapy. Rising incidence rates of keloids, along with an increasing number of cosmetic operations and heightened consumer desire for aesthetic treatments, are fueling market growth.

